The paper deals with deformable image registration, which is a common problem in medical image analysis. The proposed method uses deep learning techniques, specifically a recursive cascaded network architecture, to perform unsupervised registration. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning implies that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The recursive nature of the proposed architecture suggests that it may also be relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
